Name: Dungeon Strength RX
Description: For the Rainier Classic event hosted by Dungeon Strength RX, I designed an eye-catching and dynamic poster that perfectly captured the essence of their strength and conditioning facility. Embracing their brand identity, the poster featured bold typography and powerful images of strongmen and strongwomen showcasing their strength. With meticulous attention to detail, I included all event details and sponsor logos, creating a visually appealing and informative poster that promoted the event and its top-level competitors.

Name: Hawk Eyes
Description: Fan artwork created in collaboration with a Seattle nurse to show support for Seattle sports.

Name: J Moe da bird
Description: A talented local artist needed a simple logo to match his artist name "J Moe da Bird". This logo is used for the artist's social media, branding and marketing.

Name: K-Train Seawolves Kosei
Description: I created a striking social media graphic and highlight video to announce Tevita Kuridrani's (aka K-Train) signing with the Seattle Seawolves for Kosei Performance Partners. The artwork features a dynamic scene with the Seawolves logo, electrifying visuals, and the tagline "K-Train Tevita Kuridrani Coming Soon," capturing the excitement and power of this major signing.

Name: Oakes College
Description: Oakes College at UC Santa Cruz needed a logo to use on their website. I created a new logo and website for the Oakes College Service Learning Program working with a group of students to use websites for social change.

Name: Oakes Wedding
Description: A wedding planner needed a one-color design to give as a gift to every wedding guest in attendance. This logo was screen printed on t-shirts, sweatshirts, and tote bags.

Name: RCTB Stars and Stripes
Description: I created the "RCTB Stars and Stripes" logo for River City Travel Ball's July event. The design features patriotic elements with bold blue and red colors, highlighting the spirit of the event.

Name: Schmitt Automotive
Description: A German Automotive Specialty Shop needed a new logo for their website. I created a sleek motion graphic with a shiny German themed font.

Name: Taane Jr.
Description: A local artist, producer, and social media personality based in Seattle needed a visual designer. I designed his personal logo, business card, merchandise, and promotional content.

Name: UWAL
Description: The University of Washington Aeronautical Laboratory (UWAL) needed a logo design to be screen printed on t-shirts. I created this artwork which was sold to customers and given to employees of the wind tunnel.

Name: Valley Man of the Match
Description: I had the honor of creating a visually striking and highly engaging social media campaign for the Valley Rugby Club, celebrating and recognizing the outstanding performances of their players. The "Honorary Man of the Match" social media posts served as a testament to the club's commitment to acknowledging excellence on the field while fostering a sense of pride and recognition within the rugby community. The heart of this project lay in the dual-slide design, one dedicated to the Forwards and the other to the Backs, each featuring a player's photo and their name in bold, prominent letters. The title "Man of the Match" was proudly bestowed upon these exceptional individuals, signifying their exceptional contributions to the game. The clever use of contrasting color schemesâblue background with white text for one slide and vice versa for the otherâadded visual depth and intrigue to the posts while maintaining a cohesive brand identity. These social media graphics quickly became fan favorites, garnering a substantial amount of shares, likes, and comments. They not only celebrated individual achievements but also fostered a sense of camaraderie and motivation within the team. Recognizing these standout players not only elevated their profiles but also instilled a profound sense of pride within the Valley Rugby Club's community. In summary, this project exemplified the power of recognition and community building through thoughtful design. It celebrated the outstanding performances of players, inspired others to strive for excellence, and reinforced the club's commitment to honoring its own. It was a testament to the enduring bond and pride that define the Valley Rugby Club.

Name: Valley Rugby Matchday
Description: I had the privilege of creating a dynamic and informative graphic for the Valley Rugby Club that proved to be a game-changer in terms of engaging the team's players and followers alike. This graphic served as a powerful game announcement, capturing all the essential details in a visually appealing format. At the heart of the design were the two team logos, symbolizing the spirit of competition and unity. Positioned alongside were key pieces of information: the kickoff time and location, ensuring followers knew when and where to be to support their team. One of the standout features of this graphic was the meticulously crafted layout of text. It showcased the starting players and finishing players, cleverly numbered by their respective positions and thoughtfully separated by position groups. This not only conveyed the lineup effectively but also added a layer of professionalism and clarity to the announcement. The real magic happened when players themselves engaged with the graphic. They eagerly reposted it, proudly displaying their names in the starting roster. Their enthusiastic sharing told followers all they needed to know to attend the game, creating a buzz and anticipation within the community. This project exemplified the power of visual communication in sports, rallying the team's supporters and elevating the game-day experience. It was a testament to the club's commitment to excellence, both on and off the field.

Name: Valley Rugby Poster
Description: Recruitment Poster For the Valley Rugby Club's upcoming season, I designed a captivating poster aimed at recruiting new players and informing current members about the upcoming season. Drawing inspiration from the iconic Uncle Sam "I want you" poster, I incorporated an influential coach to lend a strong call-to-action. The poster prominently showcased the club's logo, event details, and a QR code for easy access to additional information. With a compelling design that combines tradition and modernity, the poster effectively conveyed the club's spirit and excitement for the upcoming season.

Name: Valley Rugby Schedule
Description: I designed a dynamic social media schedule graphic to keep players and fans up-to-date with match information. Emphasizing clarity and user-friendliness, the design features a clean layout that ensures easy readability. Drawing inspiration from the club's identity, I seamlessly incorporated the iconic team colors, blue and red, to maintain brand consistency. This graphic serves as a vibrant communication tool, effectively disseminating crucial information while aligning with the club's visual theme.

Name: Valley Rugby Training
Description: As part of my collaboration with the Valley Rugby Club, I created an eye-catching social media post that played a crucial role in keeping players informed and welcoming new members to our rugby family. The design features bold white lettering against a striking blue background, with the words "Rugby Training" taking center stage. Below, I included clear day, time, and location details, ensuring that players had all the essential information at a glance. To add a touch of authenticity and identity, I incorporated the Valley Kangaroo Logo, reinforcing the club's visual branding. A small label for "Fall 2023" was placed above the key details, providing context and season-specific information. Lastly, I included a prominent red text displaying the club's website link, making it easy for both current players and potential newcomers to access more information. This social media post served as a powerful communication tool, reminding existing players of training updates and extending a warm invitation to prospective members, all while maintaining the club's distinctive style and identity.

Name: Zip Line Adventure
Description: I created a fully-functional game and the artwork while taking a Game Design course at UC Santa Cruz. While taking the course, I was a guide on a zip line course suspended in the redwood trees in Santa Cruz which is where I drew inspiration for the game.
